and of course Rocket https://github.com/kusma/rocket

Currently only tested in Chrome, it's feature complete - and can read
.rocket files.

In build there's a version without any socketing, use this for releasing
your demo - only adds 4k.

commit_list.message:
Improved the rocket file parser speed

The biggest gain was had when sorting takes place after a track has been
filled, instead of sorting after every row. Took 180 seconds for a 6MB
file before, now takes 40 for 41MB.

Don't start on row zero

demo started at row 0, instead of the row Rocket is on.

commit_list.message:
Removed Websockify dependency / Bugfixes

Was able to fix the "Rocket spasms out" issue, by not sending the row on
deletions (or ctrl+z) - and not setting the row in render when the demo
is paused anyways.
Also fixed an issue, that floats in Rocket (eg 400.10) have been parsed
as int (eg 400) - both have the same "unprecision".
